<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Hi all.
I use Zend_Mail in order to read POP3 messages, extracting parts from multipart mails.</p>

<p>But in a particular mail (a confirm mail I received from voila.fr website), 'boundary' value is described like this :</p>

<p>{{Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary = bc34b90a236c267d1df0a9163df115a3b}}</p>

<p>There is a whitespace between '=' and the boundary value, so (I think) Zend_Mime_Decode::splitMessageStruct() doesn't parse boundary lines correctly.
I used the {{trim}} function on {{$boundary}} (in {{Zend_Mail_Part::_cacheContent}}), and it works, parts are well extracted, but it's a temporary solution.</p>

<p>Is there a bug in {{Zend_Mime_Decode::splitHeaderField()}}, Is this method too RFC-strict ? I'm a beginner so I'm not sure. :)</p>

<p>Edit : this issue is similar to <a href="http://framework.zend.com/issues/browse/ZF-3318">ZF-3318 issue</a>. Sorry, this one can be removed.</p>

